# 1) High-Level Objective

Process up to N links daily from a Google Sheet; archive successful rows; mark errors. N is read from YAML config.

# 2) Background / Context

See PRD: Communication Flows (Google Sheet backfill).

# 3) Assumptions & Constraints

- Columns: A=url, B=status, C=notes, D=processed_at.
- Archive tab: `Archive`.
- Daily cap is read from `agents/autopiloot/config/autopiloot.yaml` â†’ `sheets.daily_backfill_cap`.

# 4) Dependencies

- files: `agents/autopiloot/prd.mdc`
- files: `agents/autopiloot/config/autopiloot.yaml` (created by config task)

# 5) Context Plan

Beginning:

- agents/autopiloot/prd.mdc _(read-only)_
- agents/autopiloot/config/autopiloot.yaml _(read-only)_

End state:

- sheets read/write helpers; row move to Archive; cap enforced from config.

# 6) Low-Level Steps

1. Load config file `agents/autopiloot/config/autopiloot.yaml` and read `sheets.daily_backfill_cap` (default 10 if missing).
2. Read up to `daily_backfill_cap` pending rows.
3. For each, extract YouTube video(s), enqueue transcription if new.
4. On success: move row to `Archive`, set `processed_at`.
5. On failure: set `status=error` and `notes`.

# 7) Acceptance Criteria

- Rows processed sequentially; archive/remove behavior implemented.
- Errors retained on main tab.
- The number of processed rows equals the configured `daily_backfill_cap`.

